# Regression Testing Rules

## Philosophy

Every bug must become a test.

A fixed bug is not truly fixed
until a regression test protects it.

Regression tests prevent old bugs
from returning after refactor,
balance changes,
content updates,
or performance optimization.

---

# Core Rule

Bug found

↓

Reproduce

↓

Write failing test

↓

Fix bug

↓

Test passes

↓

Keep test forever

Never fix gameplay bugs
without adding regression coverage.

---

# Regression Test Goals

Protect:

- AI decisions
- Combat formulas
- Save/load integrity
- Economy transactions
- Inventory behavior
- Quest progress
- Event lifecycle
- Navigation recovery
- Offline progression
- Data migration
- Performance budgets

---

# When To Add Regression Tests

Always add regression tests for:

- Player-facing bugs
- Save corruption
- Item duplication
- Gold duplication
- Hero stuck forever
- Quest cannot complete
- Boss reward duplicated
- Inventory item lost
- Broken migration
- Crash after loading
- Economy exploit
- AI deadlock
- Performance regression

---

# Bug Report Format

Every regression should start from a bug record.

```text
Bug ID:
BUG-0001

Title:
Hero remains in COMBAT after target monster dies.

Area:
AI / Combat

Severity:
High

Steps:
1. Spawn Hero.
2. Spawn Monster.
3. Hero targets Monster.
4. Monster dies before Hero attack resolves.

Expected:
Hero clears target and chooses a new goal.

Actual:
Hero remains in COMBAT forever.

Regression Test:
GivenMonsterDiesBeforeAttack_WhenHeroUpdatesCombat_ThenHeroClearsInvalidTarget

Status:
Fixed
```

---

# Test Naming

Use Given / When / Then.

```text
GivenInventoryFull_WhenHeroLootsItem_ThenHeroReturnsToTown

GivenQuestCompleted_WhenRewardClaimedTwice_ThenSecondClaimIsRejected

GivenOldSaveVersion_WhenLoaded_ThenMigrationPreservesHeroEquipment
```

Names must describe the original bug clearly.

---

# Regression Test Location

Store tests by system.

```text
tests/
├── regression/
│   ├── ai/
│   ├── combat/
│   ├── economy/
│   ├── inventory/
│   ├── quest/
│   ├── save/
│   ├── navigation/
│   ├── offline/
│   └── performance/
```

---

# Test Metadata

Each regression test should include metadata.

```text
Bug ID
Date
System
Severity
Original Cause
Expected Behavior
```

Example:

```gdscript
# Bug ID: BUG-0042
# System: Inventory
# Severity: Critical
# Cause: Stack merge did not validate max_stack.
# Expected: Items above max_stack create a new stack.
```

---

# Reproduction First

Before fixing a bug:

1. Reproduce manually or with a script.
2. Create a failing automated test.
3. Confirm the test fails.
4. Fix the bug.
5. Confirm the test passes.

Never write the test after the fix without verifying failure first.

---

# Minimal Test Case

Regression tests should be as small as possible.

Bad:

Load full town,
spawn 100 heroes,
run 10 minutes,
verify inventory bug.

Good:

Create inventory model,
add stackable item,
verify max stack behavior.

---

# Determinism

Regression tests must be deterministic.

Use seeded RandomService.

Never depend on:

- Real time
- Rendering
- Animation timing
- Input timing
- Network timing
- Random unseeded behavior

---

# Save Regression Tests

Required for any save/load bug.

Test:

- Old save versions
- Missing fields
- Invalid values
- Duplicate IDs
- Corrupted partial data
- Migration
- Round-trip equality

Never allow save bugs
without permanent tests.

---

# Economy Regression Tests

Required for:

- Gold duplication
- Negative currency
- Missing sink
- Free upgrade
- Market exploit
- Sell/buy loop exploit
- Overflow

Every economy exploit
must have a regression test.

---

# Inventory Regression Tests

Required for:

- Item duplication
- Item loss
- Broken stack
- Equip duplication
- Sell locked item
- Invalid item ID
- Full inventory edge case

Inventory bugs are always high priority.

---

# AI Regression Tests

Required for:

- Hero idle forever
- Hero stuck in combat
- Hero cannot return town
- Hero loops between two goals
- Hero ignores low HP
- Hero ignores broken equipment
- Hero chooses unreachable zone

Every AI deadlock
must have a regression test.

---

# Navigation Regression Tests

Required for:

- Stuck path
- Unreachable destination
- Invalid gate
- Hero oscillation
- Repath loop
- Blocked road
- Zone transition bug

Navigation tests should verify
recovery behavior.

---

# Combat Regression Tests

Required for:

- Negative damage
- Infinite healing
- Cooldown bypass
- Skill spam
- Dead target attack
- Dead hero attacking
- Duplicate loot drop
- Boss reward exploit

---

# Quest Regression Tests

Required for:

- Quest cannot complete
- Quest completes twice
- Reward duplicated
- Progress lost after load
- Wrong monster counted
- Expired quest still active
- Invalid quest target

---

# Event Regression Tests

Required for:

- Event never ends
- Event starts twice
- Reward duplicated
- Event currency persists incorrectly
- NPC remains in event state
- Weather stuck
- Boss event cleanup failure

---

# Offline Regression Tests

Required for:

- Offline reward too high
- Offline reward negative
- Offline cap ignored
- Hero dies incorrectly offline
- Inventory overflow offline
- Event reward duplicated offline

---

# Performance Regression Tests

Required when a fix changes:

- AI scheduler
- Combat loop
- Navigation
- Save/load
- Inventory sorting
- UI list rendering
- Object pooling
- Event system

Track before/after metrics.

---

# Performance Regression Budget

Fail regression if:

```text
FPS drops more than 10%
Memory increases more than 15%
AI tick increases more than 20%
Combat tick increases more than 20%
Navigation failures increase
Save time exceeds 500 ms
Load time exceeds 3 sec
```

