# Severity

```text
Critical:
Save corruption, duplication exploit, crash, data loss.

High:
Hero stuck, quest blocked, boss reward bug, economy exploit.

Medium:
Wrong behavior but recoverable.

Low:
Visual or minor inconsistency.
```

---

# Regression Dashboard

Maintain a dashboard:

```text
Total Regression Tests
Passing
Failing
By System
By Severity
Recently Added
Recently Failed
Flaky Tests
```

---

# Flaky Tests

Flaky tests are bugs.

Never ignore flaky tests.

Fix by removing:

- Real time dependency
- Randomness
- Async race
- Scene timing
- External dependency

---

# CI Rules

Every Pull Request runs:

- Unit regression tests
- Save regression tests
- Economy exploit tests
- AI deadlock tests
- Data validation tests

Nightly runs:

- Simulation regression tests
- Performance regression tests
- Long-running regression tests

---

# Release Rules

A release is blocked if:

- Any Critical regression fails
- Any Save regression fails
- Any Economy exploit regression fails
- Any crash regression fails
- Any migration regression fails

---

# Regression Reports

Each CI run should output:

```text
Regression Summary
Failed Tests
Related Bug IDs
System
Severity
Recent Changes
Suggested Owner
```

---

# Regression Database

Maintain:

```text
docs/bugs/regression-log.md
```

Format:

```text
BUG-0001 | AI | High | Fixed | Test Added
BUG-0002 | Save | Critical | Fixed | Test Added
BUG-0003 | Economy | Critical | Fixed | Test Added
```

---

# Never Delete Regression Tests

Do not remove regression tests
unless the related feature is removed.

If a feature changes,
update the regression test
to protect the new expected behavior.

---

# AI Instructions

When fixing bugs:

- First create a failing regression test.
- Keep the test minimal.
- Use deterministic data.
- Include bug ID in comments.
- Add tests to the correct system folder.
- Never fix a serious bug without regression coverage.
- Explain what bug the test prevents.
- Preserve regression tests permanently.